## 5. AI-specific risks (LLMs, tool use, MCPs)

| Risk | How it applies here | Mitigation |
|------|---------------------|------------|
| Prompt injection | TODO: which inputs reach the model? | `.claude/hooks/prompt-injection-scan.sh` warns; human-in-the-loop on privileged tools |
| Insecure output handling | TODO: where does model output get executed / rendered? | Escape on render, never `eval`, sandbox shell commands |
| Training data leakage | TODO: is PII ever sent to the model? | Redact PII before prompting; use a zero-retention endpoint |
| Tool / MCP over-privilege | TODO: what scopes do MCP servers have? | Read-only tokens, filesystem MCP scoped to project root |
| Model supply chain | TODO: pinned model name? | Pin model IDs, never float `latest` |

